How do applications talk to eachother?

Applications communicate through APIs.  Most modern web applications communicate via Web Requests.

What is an API?

API stands for Application Program Interface.  An API is how an application specifies the paths and protocols that other programs can invoke to interact with your application.

What is REST?

REST is the protocol used by web requests.  REST uses urls  GET, PUT, POST, and DELETE methods to query and manipulate data at the target url.

What is a Synchronous function vs an Asyncronous Function?

A synchronous function is a function that is executed in sequential order.

An Asynchronous Function is a function that delays part of it's functionality to be executed separately from the rest of the logic in the function.
Asynchronous functions uses callbacks to report their results back to invoker.